resourceAbstractObject.default: Data from the 'Population evolution observatory' (EVOPOP): Monitoring the evolution of animal and plant populations: genetic evolution, demographic, anthropization, .... This observatory is part of the Montpellier Research Observatory of Environment (OSU OREME, oreme.org). It consists in different observing tasks: Brassica insularis ; Clape Centauree ; Common trout ; Insecticide resistance of Culex pipiens ; Wild vine.
